  sodium: 690 mg
course: main course
time required: 45m
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/cheesy-mexican-style-beef-stuffed-peppers-670d7586dc533226ca913b52
author: HelloFresh
---

Adjust rack to top position (top and middle positions for 8 servings) and preheat #oven{} to 425 degrees.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{2%tsp} in a small #pot{} (medium pot for 8) over medium-high heat. Add @tomato paste{1} and cook, stirring, until darkened in color, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Add @white rice{3/4%cup}, one of the @chicken stock concentrate{1} (two for 8), 1¼ cups water (2¼ cups for 8), and a big pinch of @salt{}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to use in Step 4.

Meanwhile, wash and dry produce.

Halve @green bell pepper{4} lengthwise; remove stems and seeds. Peel and mince or grate @garlic{3%cloves}.

Place bell peppers on a #baking sheet{} (divide between two baking sheets for 8 servings) and drizzle each half with oil; rub to coat. Season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}. Arrange cut sides down; roast on top rack (for 8, roast on top and middle racks, swapping rack positions halfway through) until tender, ~{10-15%minutes}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{2%tsp} in a large pan (for 8 servings, use two large pans or cook in batches) over medium-high heat. Add @ground beef{20%oz}, garlic, @Mexican spice blend{2%tbsp}, remaining @chicken stock concentrate{2}, @salt{} and @black pepper{}. Cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Using a #slotted spoon{}, transfer beef mixture to a large #bowl{}.

Fluff rice with a fork (it's OK if rice has a little extra liquid); transfer to bowl with beef mixture. Stir until thoroughly combined. Taste and season with salt and pepper if desired.

Once bell peppers are done roasting, remove sheet from oven. Carefully flip bell peppers and stuff each half with as much filling as will fit. Sprinkle with @Mexican cheese blend{1/2%cup}.

Heat broiler to high or increase oven to 500 degrees.

Transfer stuffed peppers to top rack and broil or roast until cheese is melted and bubbly, ~{2-4%minutes} (for 8 servings, broil or roast in batches).

> TIP: Watch carefully to avoid burning!

In a small bowl, combine @guacamole{8%tbsp} and a squeeze of @lime{3}(juiced); season with @salt{} and @black pepper{} to taste. Garnish with @cilantro{1/4%oz} and @scallions{2}. Serve with @tomato{1}.